# Add a New API Resource Skill

Use when the backend adds a new resource (e.g. `/warehouses`, `/discounts`).

## 1. Zod schema — `src/lib/schemas/<resource>.schema.ts`

- Mirror backend field names exactly — no casing transforms at the boundary
- Export response/list/create/update schemas and infer types via `z.infer<typeof schema>`
- Use `as const` maps instead of `enum`

## 2. API client — `src/lib/api/<resource>.ts`

- Import `apiRequest` from `#/lib/api/client`
- One function per HTTP verb: `listX`, `getX`, `createX`, `updateX`, `deleteX`
- Parse responses: `return xSchema.parse(await apiRequest<unknown>(…))`
- Accept `accessToken: Maybe<string>` and optional `signal?: AbortSignal`
- Co-locate query-param types (`XListQuery`) and defaults in `<resource>.constants.ts`

## 3. Permissions — `src/lib/rbac/constants/<domain>.ts`

```ts
export const WIDGET_PERMISSIONS = {
  widget_create: 'widget:create',
  widget_read: 'widget:read',
} as const
```

- Import and merge in `src/lib/rbac/constants/index.ts`
- Never use raw strings in feature code

## 4. Query keys — `src/lib/query/keys.ts`

```ts
export const widgetKeys = {
  all: ['widgets'] as const,
  lists: () => [...widgetKeys.all, 'list'] as const,
  list: (accessToken: string | null, query: WidgetListQuery) =>
    [...widgetKeys.lists(), accessToken, stableJsonKey(query)] as const,
  details: () => [...widgetKeys.all, 'detail'] as const,
  detail: (accessToken: string | null, id: string) =>
    [...widgetKeys.details(), accessToken, id] as const,
}
```

## 5. Query options — `src/lib/query/<resource>.ts`

```ts
export function widgetListQueryOptions(accessToken: Maybe<string>, query: WidgetListQuery) {
  return queryOptions({
    queryKey: widgetKeys.list(accessToken ?? null, query),
    queryFn: ({ signal }) => listWidgets(accessToken, query, signal),
    staleTime: QUERY_STALE_TIME_MS,
  })
}

export function invalidateWidgetQueries(queryClient: QueryClient): Promise<void> {
  return queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: widgetKeys.all })
}
```

## 6. Route (if user-facing)

- Add `src/routes/<path>.tsx` with loader using `context.queryClient.fetchQuery(widgetListQueryOptions(…))`
- Page component in `src/pages/<feature>/`
- See `.cursor/skills/add-route.mdc`

## 7. UI gating (if applicable)

- Wrap create/edit/delete actions in `<RequirePermission all={[WIDGET_PERMISSIONS.widget_create]}>`
- Permission-gated routes: `beforeLoad: ensurePermission({ all: […] })`

## Acceptance checklist

- [ ] `yarn tsc --noEmit` clean
- [ ] `yarn lint` clean
- [ ] API responses validated through Zod
- [ ] Query keys in `keys.ts` — none inline
- [ ] No raw permission strings
- [ ] `signal` passed through to `apiRequest`
- [ ] No `fetch` in components
